POLICE UNIVERSITY
41ST ENTRANCE CEREMONY

5
00:00:12,220 --> 00:00:16,016
ALL CHARACTER, LOCATIONS, ORGANIZATIONS,
AND EVENTS IN THIS DRAMA ARE FICTITIOUS

6
00:00:16,099 --> 00:00:17,517
KOREAN NATIONAL POLICE UNIVERSITY

7
00:00:17,600 --> 00:00:19,019
The Police University?

8
00:00:19,644 --> 00:00:20,854
Not a chance.

9
00:00:22,272 --> 00:00:23,148
Get out.

10
00:00:24,607 --> 00:00:25,859
Did you not hear me?

11
00:00:25,942 --> 00:00:28,361
You're not getting in.

12
00:00:34,242 --> 00:00:35,076
Just a moment.

13
00:00:35,744 --> 00:00:38,496
Well, I'm not sure what's going on.

14
00:00:38,580 --> 00:00:40,331
But why don't we interview him first--

15
00:00:40,415 --> 00:00:42,959
If you don't know what's going on,
please stay out of it.

16
00:00:43,042 --> 00:00:45,253
Professor Yu, watch what you say.

17
00:00:45,879 --> 00:00:47,464
We're conducting interviews here.

18
00:00:48,798 --> 00:00:50,175
That's exactly right.

19
00:00:50,675 --> 00:00:52,302
We don't know what's going on here.

20
00:00:52,802 --> 00:00:54,721
What did he do?

21
00:00:55,638 --> 00:00:58,808
It's not like he committed a crime.

22
00:00:59,476 --> 00:01:03,646
Well, is he your sworn enemy or something?

23
00:01:04,898 --> 00:01:07,609
If it's something we need to know,
please tell us now.

24
00:01:09,235 --> 00:01:10,403
Or you tell us.

25
00:01:14,991 --> 00:01:17,994
It's something personal.

26
00:01:18,578 --> 00:01:19,412
Is that so?

27
00:01:19,996 --> 00:01:24,417
If it's something personal,
you shouldn't bring it into this.

28
00:01:24,918 --> 00:01:25,752
Isn't that right?

29
00:01:27,003 --> 00:01:28,922
Can we begin the interview now?

30
00:01:38,264 --> 00:01:40,517
Please help him get in.

31
00:01:40,600 --> 00:01:41,976
Gosh, look at this.

32
00:01:42,060 --> 00:01:45,522
He did so poorly on the practical test.

33
00:01:45,605 --> 00:01:48,691
But he did pretty well
on the written exam.

34
00:01:48,775 --> 00:01:51,736
If I get in, I'll work hard
to build up my physical strength.

35
00:01:52,612 --> 00:01:55,990
Really? Then you should join
the judo club.

36
00:01:56,074 --> 00:01:57,617
-Pardon me?
-The judo club.

37
00:01:57,700 --> 00:01:59,369
Make sure you join us.

38
00:02:00,787 --> 00:02:03,581
Judo? Not everyone can do judo.

39
00:02:03,665 --> 00:02:06,292
He's so unfit. Goodness.

40
00:02:06,376 --> 00:02:08,878
You'll have to take
several English classes here.

41
00:02:08,962 --> 00:02:10,713
You should study English more.

42
00:02:10,797 --> 00:02:13,800
He can't even speak Korean properly.

43
00:02:13,883 --> 00:02:15,426
English? Come on.

44
00:02:24,602 --> 00:02:27,147
Professor Yu, why don't you
ask him a proper question?

45
00:02:33,027 --> 00:02:35,655
Do you think dirtbags like criminals
can be rehabilitated?

46
00:02:42,120 --> 00:02:42,996
Yes.

47
00:02:44,414 --> 00:02:46,875
I believe the absence of crimes
doesn't make a healthy society,

48
00:02:46,958 --> 00:02:49,252
but chances of rehabilitation do.

49
00:02:49,878 --> 00:02:52,964
Despite facing punishment, reflecting on
their wrongdoings, and making amends,

50
00:02:53,047 --> 00:02:55,091
if they are still labeled as criminals,

51
00:02:55,758 --> 00:02:59,929
they face prejudices and biases
and may end up repeating the same offense.

52
00:03:00,847 --> 00:03:02,765
-That truly breaks my heart.
-That little punk…

53
00:03:02,849 --> 00:03:05,143
On the other hand, for criminals
that show no sign of rehabilitation,

54
00:03:05,226 --> 00:03:07,770
I also agree
that they must be severely punished.

55
00:03:10,732 --> 00:03:13,693
I see. Is there anything
you'd like to say before we wrap up?

56
00:03:18,698 --> 00:03:21,618
To tell you the truth,
being a police officer isn't my dream.

57
00:03:22,952 --> 00:03:23,786
No.

58
00:03:25,246 --> 00:03:27,707
I never had anything to call "my dream."

59
00:03:29,125 --> 00:03:30,335
To me, a dream job…

60
00:03:32,587 --> 00:03:34,047
was always a blank.

61
00:03:35,924 --> 00:03:37,217
But I saw someone

62
00:03:37,842 --> 00:03:40,803
whose dream job
was getting into the Police University.

63
00:03:42,972 --> 00:03:46,142
Perhaps, I applied here
because I was copying that person.

64
00:03:47,894 --> 00:03:48,811
But…

65
00:03:50,438 --> 00:03:52,482
the fact that I now had a dream…

66
00:03:56,236 --> 00:03:58,988
My father was over the moon
when he found out about it.

67
00:04:00,573 --> 00:04:03,576
I had never seen him so happy like that.

68
00:04:06,996 --> 00:04:08,957
If I can call this desire a dream,

69
00:04:09,666 --> 00:04:11,668
I cannot give up on this dream now.

70
00:04:14,087 --> 00:04:15,505
I might not be qualified yet

71
00:04:15,588 --> 00:04:17,090
or have a long way ahead of me.

72
00:04:18,883 --> 00:04:21,177
But if you give me a chance
to achieve my belated dream,

73
00:04:22,178 --> 00:04:25,265
I will study hard and give it my all.

74
00:04:26,516 --> 00:04:27,350
I really want

75
00:04:28,268 --> 00:04:29,769
to attend the Police University.

76
00:04:42,115 --> 00:04:43,366
INTERVIEWER

77
00:04:43,950 --> 00:04:44,951
Let me borrow that.

78
00:04:58,798 --> 00:05:01,050
APPLICATION FORM

79
00:05:02,385 --> 00:05:04,804
You can't get in here, you punk.

80
00:05:07,307 --> 00:05:09,100
All right. Thank you for coming in.

81
00:05:11,311 --> 00:05:12,312
Thank you.

82
00:05:16,274 --> 00:05:17,233
That little…

83
00:05:21,988 --> 00:05:23,072
He'll pass.

84
00:05:27,952 --> 00:05:28,995
Hey, you.

85
00:05:30,163 --> 00:05:33,333
-"Hey, you"?
-Well, what was it?

86
00:05:34,500 --> 00:05:36,461
-What's your name?
-Don't you know who I am?

87
00:05:40,089 --> 00:05:42,300
Right. Didn't we meet
at Seocho Police Station?

88
00:05:42,383 --> 00:05:43,426
No.

89
00:05:45,136 --> 00:05:47,305
Right. It was the Jongno Police Station.

90
00:05:47,388 --> 00:05:48,222
No.

91
00:05:49,057 --> 00:05:51,225
The North Gyeonggi Province?
Or was it in Mapo?

92
00:05:52,518 --> 00:05:54,020
Come on. You changed a lot.

93
00:05:54,103 --> 00:05:55,897
It was Gwangjin Police Station.

94
00:05:57,690 --> 00:05:59,275
Or was it in Incheon?

95
00:06:02,070 --> 00:06:02,904
Who are you?

96
00:06:06,365 --> 00:06:08,993
All right. Why don't we take a break?

97
00:06:09,077 --> 00:06:10,119
Gosh. That punk.

98
00:06:15,374 --> 00:06:17,752
Is there Inspector Yu Dong-man?

99
00:06:17,835 --> 00:06:18,878
4 YEARS AGO

100
00:06:18,961 --> 00:06:22,673
The next model police officer
is Superintendent Kwon Hyuk-phil

101
00:06:22,757 --> 00:06:24,175
of the Administration Division.

102
00:06:28,971 --> 00:06:31,557
I believe that's Inspector Yu Dong-man.

103
00:06:31,641 --> 00:06:32,850
Hey, get a grip.

104
00:06:32,934 --> 00:06:34,811
You can't go up there, covered in blood.

105
00:06:34,894 --> 00:06:35,937
Hey!

106
00:06:37,021 --> 00:06:38,397
Let me borrow that.

107
00:06:43,236 --> 00:06:44,987
Congratulations, Inspector Yu.

108
00:06:48,449 --> 00:06:49,700
I don't need this.

109
00:06:50,952 --> 00:06:52,203
Let me say one thing.

110
00:06:53,037 --> 00:06:54,539
Do you think this stupid photo op

111
00:06:55,706 --> 00:06:58,167
can hide the fact
that it's a mess out there?

112
00:06:58,251 --> 00:07:01,587
If we had everyone in here as our backup,

113
00:07:01,671 --> 00:07:04,966
the rookie at my station
wouldn't have been stabbed today.

114
00:07:05,049 --> 00:07:05,883
Hey! Come down.

115
00:07:05,967 --> 00:07:07,552
-You know?
-Come here.

116
00:07:07,635 --> 00:07:09,428
-Come on, man.
-Let go of me.

117
00:07:10,638 --> 00:07:12,432
Model police officer, my foot!

118
00:07:13,516 --> 00:07:18,020
Real model police officers
aren't here to receive awards.

119
00:07:18,104 --> 00:07:20,148
Those who put their lives
on the line to fight the crimes

120
00:07:20,231 --> 00:07:21,858
are model police officers. Okay?

121
00:07:22,442 --> 00:07:24,444
Don't just stand there.
Get him out of here!

122
00:07:24,527 --> 00:07:26,988
-Hurry.
-Get him out of here now!

123
00:07:27,071 --> 00:07:30,366
Everyone, please calm down.

124
00:07:30,450 --> 00:07:32,326
-Let go of me!
-Hey.

125
00:07:33,744 --> 00:07:34,954
Let go!

126
00:07:35,037 --> 00:07:36,080
Hey!

127
00:07:37,165 --> 00:07:40,668
TWO DIFFERENT CLASSES OF POLICE OFFICERS

128
00:07:45,339 --> 00:07:46,299
Unbelievable.

129
00:07:47,300 --> 00:07:48,384
Gosh.

130
00:07:51,179 --> 00:07:53,222
Isn't he the detective from before?

131
00:07:53,306 --> 00:07:54,932
It's a surprise to see him here.

132
00:08:03,399 --> 00:08:05,443
Do you know who Albert Camus is?

133
00:08:06,736 --> 00:08:07,612
I don't.

134
00:08:07,695 --> 00:08:10,114
Do you know what he said?

135
00:08:10,198 --> 00:08:12,658
"Failing to punish yesterday's crime

136
00:08:12,742 --> 00:08:15,578
is equivalent to encouraging
tomorrow's crime.

137
00:08:15,661 --> 00:08:17,246
It is indeed a foolish thing."

138
00:08:17,955 --> 00:08:21,751
Right. It was foolish of me
to cut you loose.

139
00:08:21,834 --> 00:08:23,836
And our encounter here today shows

140
00:08:23,920 --> 00:08:25,588
how foolish you are
to have such a pipe dream.

141
00:08:28,508 --> 00:08:29,926
Do you know who Jonas Salk is?

142
00:08:31,260 --> 00:08:33,888
“Life is an error-making
and error-correcting process.”

143
00:08:34,889 --> 00:08:36,349
We're done here, right?

144
00:08:39,936 --> 00:08:40,937
That little…

145
00:09:03,417 --> 00:09:04,961
-My goodness.
-Look.

146
00:09:06,254 --> 00:09:07,296
So what?

147
00:09:08,297 --> 00:09:10,633
Are you here to say goodbye?
Looking like that?

148
00:09:10,716 --> 00:09:14,136
Look at you scowling at me.
Are you trying to kill me with your glare?

149
00:09:14,220 --> 00:09:15,555
Once I go to the slammer this time,

150
00:09:15,638 --> 00:09:17,723
I'll probably get out
by the time you graduate.

151
00:09:18,307 --> 00:09:19,642
I should have one last look at my wench.

152
00:09:19,725 --> 00:09:22,019
Don't call me that. You sound so ignorant.

153
00:09:22,103 --> 00:09:25,648
Fine. Good for you.
You must be happy to be so smart.

154
00:09:25,731 --> 00:09:29,986
I went through all that trouble,
so you wouldn't end up like me.

155
00:09:30,069 --> 00:09:31,779
What? I sound ignorant?

156
00:09:33,531 --> 00:09:36,325
Stop it. Or I'm going to kill myself!

157
00:09:37,201 --> 00:09:39,161
What a nasty girl you are.

158
00:09:39,245 --> 00:09:40,329
Everyone!

159
00:09:40,413 --> 00:09:44,250
My daughter tells me
she wants to die before me.

160
00:09:44,333 --> 00:09:45,793
You little…

161
00:09:56,762 --> 00:09:58,264
You darn brat.

162
00:09:58,347 --> 00:09:59,932
That's enough. Let's go.

163
00:10:00,016 --> 00:10:01,767
I gave you enough time.

164
00:10:01,851 --> 00:10:03,853
You're just a police officer, right?

165
00:10:04,437 --> 00:10:07,231
When my daughter graduates
from this school, she'll be an inspector.

166
00:10:07,315 --> 00:10:08,399
Do you know that?

167
00:10:08,482 --> 00:10:10,693
Hey. Take a good look at this jerk.

168
00:10:11,235 --> 00:10:13,112
And don't forget his face. Got it?

169
00:10:24,040 --> 00:10:25,249
Don't sell it now.

170
00:10:25,333 --> 00:10:27,710
Sell it when the gold price goes up. Okay?

171
00:10:31,339 --> 00:10:33,382
Let's go. Fine. I'll go.

172
00:10:37,470 --> 00:10:38,888
Come on. This is enough.

173
00:10:42,808 --> 00:10:44,477
I don't want you in my life!

174
00:11:09,043 --> 00:11:10,503
Just three seconds.

175
00:11:11,879 --> 00:11:14,340
It will pass if you just endure
those three seconds.

176
00:11:31,774 --> 00:11:33,943
Why do you always show up when I'm crying?

177
00:11:35,444 --> 00:11:37,696
Why do you always show up
when I'm humiliated?

178
00:11:42,660 --> 00:11:43,494
Sorry.

179
00:11:46,122 --> 00:11:47,957
Leave me alone. I don't want to see you.

180
00:11:52,962 --> 00:11:54,213
That's right.

181
00:11:54,296 --> 00:11:56,924
Only a fool would leave
when a girl tells him to leave.

182
00:11:57,925 --> 00:12:00,886
My son isn't a fool. He can never be.

183
00:12:03,764 --> 00:12:05,474
Gosh. That fool.

184
00:12:22,741 --> 00:12:23,909
My gosh.

185
00:12:27,663 --> 00:12:30,499
BESTIE

186
00:12:32,626 --> 00:12:34,920
Seung-beom probably hasn’t had dinner yet.

187
00:12:35,004 --> 00:12:36,714
He never skips a meal, you know.

188
00:12:38,299 --> 00:12:40,676
By the way, who is she?

189
00:12:40,759 --> 00:12:43,179
-Sorry?
-She's pretty, and she seemed nice.

190
00:12:44,305 --> 00:12:47,308
Do you have feelings for her?

191
00:12:49,268 --> 00:12:51,896
Is she the reason you want
to enter the Police University?

192
00:12:54,523 --> 00:12:56,525
I can tell from your look, you see.

193
00:12:56,609 --> 00:12:57,902
It's not like that.

194
00:12:57,985 --> 00:12:59,570
Don't deny it. I can tell.

195
00:13:05,951 --> 00:13:07,328
My gosh.

196
00:13:20,466 --> 00:13:21,675
Are you upset?

197
00:13:23,302 --> 00:13:25,596
Lunatic. What's there to be upset about?

198
00:13:26,263 --> 00:13:28,349
You look sullen. Mr. Yoon…

199
00:13:31,060 --> 00:13:33,312
Because Dad and I ate out without you.

200
00:13:35,022 --> 00:13:36,774
Hey. Can't I do that?

201
00:13:37,399 --> 00:13:39,068
You're being absurd, you punk.

202
00:13:45,741 --> 00:13:46,575
Why didn't you tell me?

203
00:13:47,660 --> 00:13:49,662
Did you think I'd stop you
from going to college?

204
00:13:50,829 --> 00:13:52,039
Seung-beom…

205
00:13:52,122 --> 00:13:53,999
It baffles me when I think about it.

206
00:13:54,083 --> 00:13:56,293
Why did you say yes when I asked you
to enlist in the army together?

207
00:13:57,419 --> 00:13:59,004
-Get lost if you're done.
-Hey.

208
00:14:00,172 --> 00:14:02,174
If you want to have a conversation,
just talk. Don't get angry.

209
00:14:02,258 --> 00:14:03,175
Conversation?

210
00:14:04,260 --> 00:14:05,678
Have we ever really had one?

211
00:14:05,761 --> 00:14:08,722
You never discuss anything with me.
You always tell me later.

212
00:14:08,806 --> 00:14:09,974
Damn it.

213
00:14:10,057 --> 00:14:12,768
You're always the mature one,
and I'm the ten-year-old kid.

214
00:14:15,020 --> 00:14:17,940
Don't come after me.
I'm not just upset. I'm furious.

215
00:14:26,240 --> 00:14:27,366
-Here.
-Thank you.

216
00:14:29,702 --> 00:14:34,790
I feel excited at the thought
of beginning a new semester.

217
00:14:35,416 --> 00:14:36,333
I see.

218
00:14:36,417 --> 00:14:40,379
If you stay at the school,
you'll know how I feel, Professor Yu.

219
00:14:42,965 --> 00:14:45,134
I don't ever want to know that.

220
00:14:49,013 --> 00:14:50,014
My gosh.

221
00:14:51,140 --> 00:14:52,474
Hello, professors.

222
00:14:52,558 --> 00:14:55,144
We'll start the orientation
for the new semester now.

223
00:14:55,728 --> 00:14:57,688
I'm Guidance Director, Baek Hui.

224
00:14:57,771 --> 00:15:00,983
For Public Administration,
Professor Seo Sang-hak

225
00:15:01,066 --> 00:15:03,694
will be the head professor
for freshmen as always.

226
00:15:03,777 --> 00:15:04,778
Thank you.

227
00:15:07,156 --> 00:15:09,116
Professor Choi Hee-su will be
in charge of Judo.

228
00:15:09,867 --> 00:15:11,327
I'm Choi Hee-su.

229
00:15:11,410 --> 00:15:14,705
And for Law, Professor Kwon Hyuk-phil
will be in charge.

230
00:15:14,788 --> 00:15:15,873
Thank you.

231
00:15:20,794 --> 00:15:23,255
-What is it?
-What are you doing now?

232
00:15:23,339 --> 00:15:25,758
What I'm doing now
is none of your business.

233
00:15:25,841 --> 00:15:28,218
-Well, I guess it is.
-What's up with this punk?

234
00:15:28,302 --> 00:15:29,428
And for Investigation Studies,

235
00:15:29,511 --> 00:15:31,764
the newly-appointed
Professor Yu Dong-man will be in charge.

236
00:15:31,847 --> 00:15:32,932
Jeez.

237
00:15:34,099 --> 00:15:35,643
Professor Yu Dong-man?

238
00:15:37,770 --> 00:15:38,604
Yes.

239
00:15:39,355 --> 00:15:42,274
Right. I'm Yu Dong-man.

240
00:15:42,358 --> 00:15:43,734
I got an important call.

241
00:15:46,195 --> 00:15:47,488
He got a call.

242
00:15:47,988 --> 00:15:50,199
-For policy analysis…
-Are you at the school now?

243
00:15:50,866 --> 00:15:53,410
Goodness, you adapt so quickly.

244
00:15:53,494 --> 00:15:56,080
Gosh, I guess I've gone too easy
on you these days.

245
00:15:56,163 --> 00:15:58,499
They will recruit more officers
in two weeks.

246
00:15:58,582 --> 00:16:01,835
If you lose this chance,
you can't come back even if you want to.

247
00:16:02,878 --> 00:16:04,296
Darn it…

248
00:16:08,175 --> 00:16:09,510
Hello.

249
00:16:09,593 --> 00:16:11,303
Here are your drinks.

250
00:16:11,387 --> 00:16:13,597
My goodness. This is really…

251
00:16:13,681 --> 00:16:14,848
Hold on.

252
00:16:14,932 --> 00:16:17,476
This is the signature drink of Gossi Beer.

253
00:16:17,559 --> 00:16:19,645
-You have to taste it as it is…
-I'm mixing it with soju.

254
00:16:21,146 --> 00:16:22,523
Me too.

255
00:16:23,649 --> 00:16:25,985
Then you should have ordered
a bottled beer.

256
00:16:30,572 --> 00:16:31,573
What's wrong with him?

257
00:16:33,033 --> 00:16:33,909
So what?

258
00:16:34,743 --> 00:16:36,412
What do you mean, "so what"?

259
00:16:36,495 --> 00:16:39,873
We're tracking several
cryptocurrency exchanges now.

260
00:16:39,957 --> 00:16:43,460
We expect it'll take three months
to track them down.

261
00:16:44,253 --> 00:16:46,630
Three months?
Not three days or three weeks?

262
00:16:46,714 --> 00:16:48,632
Do you know how many
cryptocurrency exchanges there are?

263
00:16:48,716 --> 00:16:51,301
We don't have enough budget to start with,

264
00:16:51,385 --> 00:16:53,012
and I'm doing all the work.
It's killing me.

265
00:16:53,095 --> 00:16:55,973
Don't you see how haggard I look?

266
00:17:00,561 --> 00:17:02,730
-You've always looked like that.
-You…

267
00:17:03,313 --> 00:17:04,398
Just…

268
00:17:04,481 --> 00:17:06,942
Get down on your knees
and apologize to Captain…

269
00:17:07,026 --> 00:17:07,901
Are you insane?

270
00:17:08,402 --> 00:17:10,154
This is about my pride now.

271
00:17:10,237 --> 00:17:13,240
Your pride, my foot.
You just don't want to lose face.

272
00:17:13,323 --> 00:17:14,825
And even if we find them,

273
00:17:14,908 --> 00:17:17,453
we can't track their accounts
since they've changed the exchange.

274
00:17:18,370 --> 00:17:20,622
We have to ask Yoon now.

275
00:17:21,415 --> 00:17:24,168
We must catch those jerks.

276
00:17:27,171 --> 00:17:28,213
Dong-man.

277
00:17:28,297 --> 00:17:29,882
Is this about
the 100 million won you lost?

278
00:17:29,965 --> 00:17:31,008
What did you say?

279
00:17:31,091 --> 00:17:34,887
Well, even if that's the case,
I honestly can't understand.

280
00:17:34,970 --> 00:17:36,472
You didn't even care about this case.

281
00:17:36,555 --> 00:17:39,058
The case belonged to Cybercrimes
in the first place.

282
00:17:39,141 --> 00:17:40,142
My gosh.

283
00:17:41,935 --> 00:17:43,062
Or…

284
00:17:43,729 --> 00:17:46,607
is it because of the person
who died in the accident?

285
00:17:47,816 --> 00:17:49,485
Shut your mouth, you punk.

286
00:17:52,404 --> 00:17:53,572
Seriously…

287
00:17:55,157 --> 00:17:58,827
My gut feeling tells me
that this case is dangerous.

288
00:17:58,911 --> 00:18:01,497
Who are you to talk about the gut feeling?

289
00:18:01,580 --> 00:18:02,623
Gosh.

290
00:18:03,957 --> 00:18:06,543
I was going to tell you this
when I have clear evidence.

291
00:18:06,627 --> 00:18:08,796
They shut down the casino.

292
00:18:08,879 --> 00:18:11,799
They keep slipping away.
There's something fishy about it.

293
00:18:11,882 --> 00:18:15,594
I think this is out of our league.

294
00:18:19,932 --> 00:18:23,018
You're writing a scenario
instead of working.

295
00:18:23,102 --> 00:18:24,311
My gosh, seriously.

296
00:18:25,270 --> 00:18:27,314
This is my gut feeling
as a police officer.

297
00:18:27,397 --> 00:18:30,275
Your gut feeling, my foot.
Stop that nonsense.

298
00:18:30,359 --> 00:18:32,152
What? "This is out of our league?"

299
00:18:32,236 --> 00:18:34,947
How could you talk like that
as a police officer?

300
00:18:35,030 --> 00:18:35,948
Gosh, seriously.

301
00:18:36,532 --> 00:18:39,118
There's one more, you punk.

302
00:18:39,201 --> 00:18:40,244
My gosh.

303
00:18:43,872 --> 00:18:45,290
You're not going to talk to me?

304
00:18:46,542 --> 00:18:48,752
Do you want me to apologize this time too?

305
00:18:51,004 --> 00:18:51,880
What did you say?

306
00:18:57,719 --> 00:18:59,763
Enough. Let's stop this.

307
00:19:01,348 --> 00:19:02,474
It's not over.

308
00:19:04,768 --> 00:19:07,229
-You little…
-I told you to stop.

309
00:19:08,438 --> 00:19:10,899
-I told you to stop.
-Bring it on, you punk.

310
00:19:24,037 --> 00:19:25,455
Do you still think I'm a loser?

311
00:19:26,165 --> 00:19:28,959
Answer me. Do you still think I'm a loser?

312
00:19:30,669 --> 00:19:33,172
If you can't give me that punch,
you're really a loser.

313
00:19:33,255 --> 00:19:35,757
Hit me. I said to hit me!

314
00:19:37,885 --> 00:19:40,637
"It's none of your business
whether I go to college or not."

315
00:19:41,138 --> 00:19:42,431
"Did the interview go well?"

316
00:19:42,514 --> 00:19:44,766
"I hope you get in."
Shouldn't that come first?

317
00:19:46,476 --> 00:19:47,686
Can you call yourself my friend?

318
00:19:47,769 --> 00:19:49,271
Can you call yourself my brother?

319
00:19:49,354 --> 00:19:52,107
You're a loser
who can't even say that stuff.

320
00:19:52,191 --> 00:19:54,151
Go ahead. Hit me, jerk.

321
00:19:54,234 --> 00:19:55,903
What about you?

322
00:19:55,986 --> 00:19:57,404
You've done judo for ten years.

323
00:19:57,487 --> 00:20:00,032
You can obviously beat me and put me down.

324
00:20:00,115 --> 00:20:02,034
But you let me give a beating
and fall on purpose.

325
00:20:02,117 --> 00:20:03,160
Even now, you're going easy on me.

326
00:20:03,243 --> 00:20:05,287
You're a loser, you punk.

327
00:20:08,290 --> 00:20:10,542
Would you stop losing?

328
00:20:12,544 --> 00:20:13,879
I won't lose anymore.

329
00:20:13,962 --> 00:20:15,380
I'll never lose!

330
00:20:31,313 --> 00:20:32,648
Are you hurt?

331
00:20:33,982 --> 00:20:35,776
It must hurt. Let me see.

332
00:20:36,610 --> 00:20:38,195
You lunatic.

333
00:20:43,742 --> 00:20:44,910
How was your interview?

334
00:20:45,786 --> 00:20:47,371
I did well, you punk.

335
00:20:47,454 --> 00:20:49,915
Congratulations, you punk.

336
00:20:51,500 --> 00:20:52,834
That crazy punk.

337
00:20:57,589 --> 00:20:58,715
Hold on a second.

338
00:21:02,344 --> 00:21:03,470
WISH FOR ADMISSION

339
00:21:04,221 --> 00:21:05,889
It's here.

340
00:21:11,895 --> 00:21:14,940
"You have passed
the 2021 Freshman Admission Examination."

341
00:21:15,023 --> 00:21:19,069
"You have been admitted
to Korean National Police University."

342
00:21:19,152 --> 00:21:20,570
-"Admitted!"
-Goodness. Hey.

343
00:21:20,654 --> 00:21:22,656
Oh, my gosh.

344
00:21:22,739 --> 00:21:24,908
WISH FOR ADMISSION

345
00:21:25,617 --> 00:21:27,411
I've been admitted.

346
00:21:27,494 --> 00:21:30,080
Yes! I'm going to be a police officer!

347
00:21:32,874 --> 00:21:35,002
Why do you check it over and over again?

348
00:21:35,085 --> 00:21:36,628
Can't you see it says "admitted"?

349
00:21:36,712 --> 00:21:38,297
Your second son
is going to be a police officer.

350
00:21:38,380 --> 00:21:40,048
A grade six civil servant.

351
00:21:48,890 --> 00:21:49,975
Dad, really?

352
00:21:51,685 --> 00:21:52,936
Are you going to open it?

353
00:21:58,275 --> 00:21:59,276
Here.

354
00:22:02,529 --> 00:22:03,530
What is it?

355
00:22:04,698 --> 00:22:05,824
It's a spam message.

356
00:22:06,908 --> 00:22:08,577
Hold on a second.

357
00:22:10,746 --> 00:22:12,539
MILITARY MANPOWER ADMINISTRATION

358
00:22:12,622 --> 00:22:14,499
MR. YOON SEUNG-BEOM,

359
00:22:14,583 --> 00:22:16,501
CONGRATULATIONS
ON JOINING THE MARINE CORPS

360
00:22:16,585 --> 00:22:17,502
Congratulations.

361
00:22:21,798 --> 00:22:23,175
Talk about perfect timing.

362
00:22:24,718 --> 00:22:25,761
Well done.

363
00:22:26,303 --> 00:22:28,346
-Here.
-I want some too, Dad!

364
00:22:28,430 --> 00:22:29,806
Don't drink without me.

365
00:22:42,569 --> 00:22:44,821
Get going. Give Sun-ho a ride, Dad.

366
00:22:45,489 --> 00:22:47,532
I can go by myself.
You should see Seung-beom off.

367
00:22:48,116 --> 00:22:49,785
I have a work trip, so I should get going.

368
00:22:50,452 --> 00:22:53,538
Take good care of yourself, both of you.

369
00:22:58,585 --> 00:23:01,963
Seriously. If you grow old like that,
you'll be all alone and lonely!

370
00:23:04,132 --> 00:23:05,425
We'll call you, Dad!

371
00:23:12,974 --> 00:23:13,934
You should get going.

372
00:23:23,610 --> 00:23:24,820
Seung-beom!

373
00:23:29,658 --> 00:23:31,034
What? What is it?

374
00:23:34,287 --> 00:23:37,499
Go to college
when you complete your military service.

375
00:23:38,583 --> 00:23:40,877
I'll attend your college entrance ceremony
no matter what.

376
00:23:41,545 --> 00:23:43,255
I'll be there at all costs,

377
00:23:43,922 --> 00:23:45,006
so go to college.

378
00:23:46,174 --> 00:23:48,218
-Hey.
-Promise me that you will.

379
00:23:49,427 --> 00:23:51,555
I was going to anyway, you twerp.

380
00:23:51,638 --> 00:23:53,765
Did you think you'd be the only one
with a college degree?

381
00:23:56,101 --> 00:23:57,102
And Kang Sun-ho.

382
00:24:00,021 --> 00:24:01,022
Isn't that your train?

383
00:24:01,606 --> 00:24:02,983
What are you talking about?

384
00:24:04,025 --> 00:24:05,777
-Hey.
-Hurry!

385
00:24:10,115 --> 00:24:12,117
Car 17, seat number 8C.

386
00:24:13,952 --> 00:24:15,495
Okay, it's here.

387
00:24:26,715 --> 00:24:27,549
You can have it.

388
00:24:30,135 --> 00:24:30,969
Thanks.

389
00:24:50,989 --> 00:24:52,032
You must be thirsty.

390
00:24:52,657 --> 00:24:54,075
I'll go get something quickly.

391
00:24:54,159 --> 00:24:54,993
No, it's okay.

392
00:24:55,076 --> 00:24:57,037
-I'll be quick.
-No, don't bother.

393
00:24:59,748 --> 00:25:00,582
Sorry.

394
00:25:01,625 --> 00:25:03,752
Then I'll get you water
whenever you're thirsty

395
00:25:03,835 --> 00:25:05,462
during our training.

396
00:25:06,129 --> 00:25:06,963
Why?

397
00:25:10,342 --> 00:25:12,219
I'm just so happy to see you again.

398
00:25:13,261 --> 00:25:16,306
I want to do whatever I can
to see you once more.

399
00:25:34,491 --> 00:25:36,701
What? Speak.

400
00:25:38,578 --> 00:25:40,288
-What?
-Go ahead and speak.

401
00:25:42,499 --> 00:25:44,000
No. It's nothing.

402
00:25:44,918 --> 00:25:46,419
I can carry this for you, your suitcase.

403
00:25:47,462 --> 00:25:48,546
Okay?

404
00:25:49,422 --> 00:25:50,382
Sure, if you want to.

405
00:25:50,465 --> 00:25:52,008
All right, I'll carry it for you.

406
00:25:55,887 --> 00:25:57,264
Hold on.

407
00:26:00,225 --> 00:26:01,309
Hang on.

408
00:26:03,311 --> 00:26:04,604
Hey, I got it.

409
00:26:04,688 --> 00:26:06,856
No, I can do it.

410
00:26:06,940 --> 00:26:08,108
I should just wheel it.

411
00:26:10,902 --> 00:26:12,862
Why is this stuck?

412
00:26:24,165 --> 00:26:25,792
Are you freshmen at the Police University?

413
00:26:25,875 --> 00:26:26,793
What?

414
00:26:27,419 --> 00:26:28,503
Yes.

415
00:26:32,007 --> 00:26:33,425
Me too.

416
00:26:33,508 --> 00:26:35,593
I'll carry this
to the meeting spot for you.

417
00:26:37,137 --> 00:26:40,015
No, it's okay. I can carry it myself.

418
00:26:48,440 --> 00:26:49,774
Darn it.

419
00:26:51,109 --> 00:26:52,110
It's nice to meet you all.

420
00:26:52,694 --> 00:26:55,363
I'm Guidance Director Baek Hui
at the Police University.

421
00:26:55,447 --> 00:26:58,033
For the next two weeks, you'll partake
in our Chungram Training Program.

422
00:26:58,116 --> 00:26:59,534
Chung as in "blue",
and ram as in "cradle".

423
00:26:59,617 --> 00:27:02,620
It encapsulates our determination
to grow talent in this cradle.

424
00:27:02,704 --> 00:27:05,999
But unlike its beautiful name,
this intense, rigorous training program

425
00:27:06,082 --> 00:27:09,085
will make you think of your mother
at every moment.

426
00:27:09,169 --> 00:27:10,337
But you must stay strong

427
00:27:11,087 --> 00:27:11,963
and get through it.

428
00:27:12,839 --> 00:27:14,132
The future of the police.

429
00:27:14,215 --> 00:27:16,509
That's you.

430
00:27:17,302 --> 00:27:19,262
I hope all of you
complete the training successfully

431
00:27:19,346 --> 00:27:22,515
without anyone getting hurt or giving up.

432
00:27:24,309 --> 00:27:25,477
Applause, please.

433
00:27:32,817 --> 00:27:35,111
What can I do to return to the precinct?

434
00:27:35,195 --> 00:27:36,529
All this is driving me crazy.

435
00:27:38,656 --> 00:27:40,408
THE CHUNGRAM TRAINING ENTRANCE CEREMONY

436
00:27:45,705 --> 00:27:46,748
That punk.

437
00:27:51,002 --> 00:27:52,420
I can't believe you actually came here.

438
00:27:58,301 --> 00:27:59,844
Do you think I'm a joke?

439
00:28:00,720 --> 00:28:02,889
I honestly don't understand
why you're being like this.

440
00:28:03,431 --> 00:28:05,683
You told me I should repay my dad
for the rest of my life.

441
00:28:05,767 --> 00:28:07,310
Yes, that's right.

442
00:28:07,894 --> 00:28:09,521
But you said yourself

443
00:28:09,604 --> 00:28:13,358
that life is a process where one works
on correcting one's mistakes.

444
00:28:13,441 --> 00:28:15,610
I'm trying to correct my mistake here.

445
00:28:15,693 --> 00:28:17,862
Letting you off like that
was clearly a mistake.

446
00:28:19,364 --> 00:28:21,533
You can't get into this school, you punk.

447
00:28:21,616 --> 00:28:24,994
You won't even be able
to set foot in here after this.

448
00:28:25,078 --> 00:28:26,037
Do you understand?

449
00:28:26,621 --> 00:28:29,499
I've already been admitted.

450
00:28:31,209 --> 00:28:32,460
We'll see about that.

451
00:28:40,552 --> 00:28:42,011
WELCOME TO THE CHUNGRAM TRAINING PROGRAM

452
00:28:42,095 --> 00:28:43,054
It's so nice here.

453
00:28:44,347 --> 00:28:45,724
This is so awesome.

454
00:28:47,142 --> 00:28:48,768
This is the Police University.

455
00:28:53,231 --> 00:28:54,858
-Hey!
-Gosh.

456
00:28:54,941 --> 00:28:56,609
I knew you'd get in.

457
00:28:57,569 --> 00:29:00,029
Right? It's so nice to see you again.

458
00:29:01,156 --> 00:29:02,031
I'm Noh Beom-tae.

459
00:29:03,992 --> 00:29:07,370
I can't believe you actually came here.

460
00:29:07,954 --> 00:29:12,083
By the way, how do you know
Professor Yu Dong-man?

461
00:29:14,502 --> 00:29:15,545
I met him a while back.

462
00:29:15,628 --> 00:29:17,088
Lucky you!

463
00:29:17,714 --> 00:29:20,800
They say connections
are everything in this country.

464
00:29:21,301 --> 00:29:23,094
-We're more like enemies.
-What?

465
00:29:23,178 --> 00:29:24,846
We're set after this training, right?

466
00:29:24,929 --> 00:29:28,099
What? This is only the beginning, buddy.

467
00:29:28,600 --> 00:29:30,935
Let's get through the training

468
00:29:31,019 --> 00:29:33,855
and make it to
the final admission stage. Okay?

469
00:29:33,938 --> 00:29:34,939
-Sounds good.
-Yes!

470
00:29:35,023 --> 00:29:37,233
Wait, we can be disqualified
even at this stage?

471
00:29:37,317 --> 00:29:40,403
Of course. I guess you came here
not knowing anything.

472
00:29:40,487 --> 00:29:43,448
Tons of people give up
during the Chungram Training.

473
00:29:55,752 --> 00:29:57,045
If you get
on the drill instructor's bad side,

474
00:29:57,629 --> 00:29:59,297
you won't even last two days.

475
00:30:01,466 --> 00:30:03,593
I wonder which professor
will be our drill instructor.

476
00:30:03,676 --> 00:30:05,970
Give us someone who's easygoing, please.

477
00:30:39,796 --> 00:30:42,340
Nice to meet you.
I'm Senior Inspector Yu Dong-man.

478
00:30:42,423 --> 00:30:44,968
I'll be guiding you guys
through the entire training.

479
00:30:45,051 --> 00:30:46,177
Let me warn you first.

480
00:30:46,261 --> 00:30:48,304
Don't stand out and behave yourself.

481
00:30:48,888 --> 00:30:51,099
Stay out of trouble
and focus on the training.

482
00:30:51,766 --> 00:30:54,727
If I spot you doing anything funny,
you'll be disqualified.

483
00:30:57,730 --> 00:30:58,773
No exceptions.

484
00:31:01,442 --> 00:31:03,695
We will now begin the training.

485
00:31:06,531 --> 00:31:07,532
-Fifty-one!
-Fifty-one!

486
00:31:08,199 --> 00:31:09,284
-Fifty-two!
-Fifty-two!

487
00:31:09,951 --> 00:31:11,327
-Fifty-three!
-Do it properly!

488
00:31:11,411 --> 00:31:13,079
-Fifty-four!
-Arms all the way up!

489
00:31:13,162 --> 00:31:14,789
-Fifty-five.
-Watch your elbows!

490
00:31:14,873 --> 00:31:16,249
-Fifty-six.
-Do it right!

491
00:31:16,332 --> 00:31:17,375
-Yes, sir!
-Fifty-seven!

492
00:31:17,876 --> 00:31:20,837
-Hey. How much longer…
-I can't hear you!

493
00:31:20,920 --> 00:31:23,131
How much longer must we do this?

494
00:31:23,214 --> 00:31:26,426
Don't tell me
this will end with one of us dying.

495
00:31:26,509 --> 00:31:28,344
Who's talking right now?

496
00:31:28,428 --> 00:31:30,263
-Raise your arms.
-Do you want to go home?

497
00:31:30,346 --> 00:31:32,348
-Line up.
-Halt!

498
00:31:34,642 --> 00:31:36,477
-Kang Sun-ho, you're the center.
-Center!

499
00:31:36,561 --> 00:31:39,063
-Gather around him.
-One, two.

500
00:31:43,234 --> 00:31:47,155
You will divide into
three autonomous units from this point on.

501
00:31:47,238 --> 00:31:49,490
You will move, stay, and train together.

502
00:31:50,491 --> 00:31:53,202
And every unit will have a unit captain.

503
00:31:53,286 --> 00:31:55,413
If your unit members fail
to keep up with the training,

504
00:31:55,496 --> 00:31:58,166
the captains will be responsible
for everyone's failure.

505
00:31:58,249 --> 00:31:59,500
Don't forget that.

506
00:32:00,084 --> 00:32:04,923
Despite this huge risk, is there anyone
who's brave enough to volunteer?

507
00:32:08,426 --> 00:32:11,429
You all applied to become police officers
to protect our people.

508
00:32:11,930 --> 00:32:13,097
Do we only have cowards here?

509
00:32:14,599 --> 00:32:16,267
Trainee Park Min-gyu!

510
00:32:16,851 --> 00:32:17,769
I'll do my best!

511
00:32:19,646 --> 00:32:21,064
What about the second unit?

512
00:32:22,732 --> 00:32:25,276
Trainee Oh Kang-hui.
I would like to volunteer.

513
00:32:25,360 --> 00:32:26,235
Great.

514
00:32:27,153 --> 00:32:30,990
All right. For the caption
of the third unit…

515
00:32:49,759 --> 00:32:51,135
You over there.

516
00:32:52,345 --> 00:32:53,346
Pardon?

517
00:32:56,265 --> 00:32:57,558
-Me?
-Yes.

518
00:32:58,559 --> 00:33:00,144
It looks like you could use some courage.

519
00:33:00,228 --> 00:33:02,689
So you will be the captain
