I would have already been dead

779
00:51:15,947 --> 00:51:17,866
or committed suicide by now.

780
00:51:17,949 --> 00:51:20,827
Like he said, we shouldn't have this.

781
00:51:23,538 --> 00:51:25,624
Throwing away food is a sin.

782
00:51:25,707 --> 00:51:27,709
We'll finish it in 30 seconds. Okay?

783
00:51:48,480 --> 00:51:49,689
Who's that there?

784
00:51:52,150 --> 00:51:53,068
Who's there?

785
00:51:55,237 --> 00:51:56,238
-Go.
-What's going on?

786
00:51:56,947 --> 00:51:58,114
What do we do?

787
00:52:01,827 --> 00:52:03,995
-Sun-ho.
-Come on.

788
00:52:09,209 --> 00:52:10,085
Sun-ho?

789
00:52:11,169 --> 00:52:13,755
What are you doing here?
What are you hiding in the back?

790
00:52:14,881 --> 00:52:16,049
What is it?

791
00:52:17,300 --> 00:52:18,552
Did you just get in my way?

792
00:52:22,681 --> 00:52:24,057
You're eating instant noodles?

793
00:52:25,183 --> 00:52:26,142
Come with me.

794
00:52:27,143 --> 00:52:28,144
Come out!

795
00:52:34,818 --> 00:52:37,320
OUR COUNTRY HAS FAITH
IN THOSE OF YOU WHO PASS HERE

796
00:52:40,866 --> 00:52:41,950
Let's meet.

797
00:52:42,033 --> 00:52:44,327
I need to talk to you
about something in person.

798
00:53:05,557 --> 00:53:07,893
Answer me right now. Who were the others?

799
00:53:11,730 --> 00:53:13,857
I see. So you'll take the fall
for everyone?

800
00:53:15,817 --> 00:53:18,778
Fine. Let's see
when you'll give up on that idea.

801
00:53:18,862 --> 00:53:20,071
Run 30 laps around the field.

802
00:53:35,503 --> 00:53:37,881
Let's just go and tell him the truth.

803
00:53:38,798 --> 00:53:40,508
At this rate, Sun-ho really might die.

804
00:53:41,426 --> 00:53:44,012
Right. We should just
go through the drills with him at least.

805
00:53:46,389 --> 00:53:47,599
Stop.

806
00:53:47,682 --> 00:53:48,808
Goodness.

807
00:53:50,143 --> 00:53:51,311
Darn it.

808
00:54:04,950 --> 00:54:08,203
Why don't you just be yourself?

809
00:54:08,286 --> 00:54:11,373
You let me hide behind you
and helped Beom-tae today.

810
00:54:12,707 --> 00:54:13,708
That's you.

811
00:54:15,001 --> 00:54:16,044
Look at that.

812
00:54:17,379 --> 00:54:19,047
Keep running
until you give me their names.

813
00:54:31,977 --> 00:54:33,395
I was alone!

814
00:54:36,147 --> 00:54:38,066
Hey, do you think I'm a joke?

815
00:54:38,817 --> 00:54:40,276
Should I check the CCTV footage?

816
00:54:40,360 --> 00:54:45,991
Be it 100 or 200 laps.
I will face all the drills by myself!

817
00:54:46,074 --> 00:54:47,951
I should have stopped them
as their captain.

818
00:54:48,034 --> 00:54:49,369
But I couldn't say no.

819
00:54:49,452 --> 00:54:51,496
It was my mistake
to have eaten it with them.

820
00:54:52,747 --> 00:54:56,626
As the captain of the unit,
I have been an embarrassment.

821
00:54:57,127 --> 00:55:00,547
I don't want my fellow unit members
to see me mess up again.

822
00:55:00,630 --> 00:55:03,341
Please let me face the drills by myself!

823
00:55:04,551 --> 00:55:06,428
You're nothing but all talk.

824
00:55:09,806 --> 00:55:10,807
Han Min-guk.

825
00:55:11,975 --> 00:55:13,393
Go inside and do the roll call.

826
00:55:14,102 --> 00:55:14,978
Yes, sir.

827
00:55:19,899 --> 00:55:21,860
You're still not going
to leave voluntarily?

828
00:55:23,778 --> 00:55:25,530
-Answer me.
-Why?

829
00:55:27,782 --> 00:55:28,825
Why can't I stay?

830
00:55:33,955 --> 00:55:36,958
All you ever did was have
some instant noodles with your friends.

831
00:55:37,042 --> 00:55:40,045
So do you think this treatment
is unfair to you? Is it?

832
00:55:42,047 --> 00:55:43,590
Wake up, punk.

833
00:55:44,507 --> 00:55:48,386
To you, this is all too easy.
Breaking the rules comes easy to you.

834
00:55:48,470 --> 00:55:50,055
Doing things that you're not supposed to.

835
00:55:50,138 --> 00:55:51,473
I don't think that's true.

836
00:55:51,556 --> 00:55:52,807
That's not true?

837
00:55:53,641 --> 00:55:54,559
How is it not true?

838
00:55:54,642 --> 00:55:58,146
Can't you just think of it
as a mistake and let it go?

839
00:56:00,315 --> 00:56:01,441
It wasn't your first time.

840
00:56:03,860 --> 00:56:07,197
You've done it more than once, you punk.

841
00:56:10,283 --> 00:56:13,078
Dad won't have cancer now. No more cancer.

842
00:56:15,163 --> 00:56:16,206
What should I do?

843
00:56:22,545 --> 00:56:23,880
GO TO COLLEGE!

844
00:56:27,717 --> 00:56:29,010
NEW REMITTANCE 5,000,000 WON

845
00:56:29,094 --> 00:56:31,930
Gosh. That crazy jerk.
Where did he get this much money?

846
00:56:38,478 --> 00:56:40,814
You took out 7 million won at 7:15 p.m.

847
00:56:40,897 --> 00:56:43,441
And you took out
5 million won at 7:18 p.m.

848
00:56:46,236 --> 00:56:49,239
The first time is hard.
It's easy the next time around.

849
00:56:50,156 --> 00:56:52,408
And by the third time,
you won't even feel guilty.

850
00:56:52,992 --> 00:56:55,328
But you want to be a police officer?

851
00:56:57,914 --> 00:57:00,291
Do you get why you can't be a cop now?

852
00:57:01,543 --> 00:57:04,129
And why you don't deserve
to attend the Police University?

853
00:57:07,132 --> 00:57:09,509
What? "A belated dream"?

854
00:57:10,135 --> 00:57:11,636
Goodness. You're all talk.

855
00:57:14,806 --> 00:57:15,682
No excuses?

856
00:57:18,726 --> 00:57:21,438
I have nothing to say. I'm sorry.

857
00:57:21,521 --> 00:57:23,273
I see, okay.

858
00:57:24,357 --> 00:57:26,609
I was going to rip your mouth
if you gave any.

859
00:57:28,653 --> 00:57:31,823
I told you it's wrong to stay here
when you don't deserve it.

860
00:57:31,906 --> 00:57:35,118
I also said not learning your place
and acting cheeky was also wrong.

861
00:57:37,579 --> 00:57:38,621
Get out on your own.

862
00:57:41,291 --> 00:57:44,377
-I'm sorry.
-Leave, you punk.

863
00:57:46,754 --> 00:57:49,507
I'm sorry. Please give me a chance.

864
00:57:51,801 --> 00:57:53,595
I will never break the rule again.

865
00:57:53,678 --> 00:57:55,388
I will follow the rules.

866
00:57:55,472 --> 00:57:58,975
I will change myself to become someone
that belongs to the Police University.

867
00:57:59,893 --> 00:58:01,144
Just one chance.

868
00:58:01,728 --> 00:58:04,606
Please give me one last chance. Please?

869
00:58:08,651 --> 00:58:12,238
You also need to be worthy
of a second chance.

870
00:58:12,906 --> 00:58:14,532
And you're not worthy of it.

871
00:58:26,294 --> 00:58:28,671
The captain kept saying
that we shouldn't eat it.

872
00:58:29,214 --> 00:58:31,049
We were the ones who wanted to eat it.

873
00:58:31,132 --> 00:58:32,592
It's not Sun-ho's fault.

874
00:58:33,885 --> 00:58:35,595
Sun-ho wouldn't be
going through the drills

875
00:58:35,678 --> 00:58:37,347
if he gave away our names.

876
00:58:38,014 --> 00:58:40,850
He wanted to protect us.
Please don't scold him.

877
00:58:51,611 --> 00:58:53,863
-What is it?
-Don't be shocked.

878
00:58:53,947 --> 00:58:56,908
It's about
your little hacker friend, Yoon.

879
00:58:57,408 --> 00:58:58,910
Yes. Did you find him?

880
00:59:01,788 --> 00:59:02,622
It's Kang Sun-ho.

881
00:59:04,082 --> 00:59:06,042
What are you talking about?

882
00:59:06,125 --> 00:59:09,671
Don't you remember Kang Sun-ho,
the kid we rounded up a while ago?

883
00:59:09,754 --> 00:59:12,298
He was your hacker friend, Yoon.

884
00:59:12,882 --> 00:59:16,469
I can't believe your online friend
turned out to be your enemy in real life.

885
00:59:17,428 --> 00:59:21,349
This must put you in a tight spot.
You know?

886
00:59:32,527 --> 00:59:34,862
How can that jerk be…

887
00:59:51,170 --> 00:59:53,089
If I need to be worthy of a second chance,

888
00:59:54,716 --> 00:59:57,969
I will prove it by leading my unit
to victory in the last training.

889
00:59:59,762 --> 01:00:01,598
And if I fail to prove it then,

890
01:00:02,265 --> 01:00:03,725
I will withdraw

891
01:00:05,059 --> 01:00:06,144
without making any excuses.

892
01:00:08,313 --> 01:00:12,900
So can you please
decide after the training?

893
01:00:13,776 --> 01:00:15,778
Whether I deserve to stay in this school

894
01:00:16,696 --> 01:00:17,530
or not.

895
01:00:58,613 --> 01:01:00,948
A miracle? A surprise?
If that's what you're hoping for, wake up.

896
01:01:01,032 --> 01:01:02,617
Can't I even hope for them?

897
01:01:02,700 --> 01:01:04,118
Just get to the point
and say you want me out.

898
01:01:04,202 --> 01:01:06,496
I got into the Police University.

899
01:01:06,579 --> 01:01:08,706
Look at this brat,
he keeps talking as if we're buddies.

900
01:01:08,790 --> 01:01:10,124
What will you do about Kang Sun-ho?

901
01:01:10,208 --> 01:01:12,210
"Follow my heart"? What's her deal?

902
01:01:12,293 --> 01:01:13,503
-Who?
-What?

903
01:01:13,586 --> 01:01:15,380
Who's the girl you have a crush on?

904
01:01:15,463 --> 01:01:17,173
I'll tell you
once we're officially admitted.

905
01:01:17,256 --> 01:01:19,092
Then I should be
rooting for your unit too.

906
01:01:19,175 --> 01:01:20,343
I refuse to leave.

907
01:01:20,426 --> 01:01:21,594
I will get in, no matter what.

908
01:01:21,678 --> 01:01:22,637
You won't give up, right?

909
01:01:22,720 --> 01:01:24,305
Cheol-jin. Hey, Cheol-jin!

910
01:01:25,473 --> 01:01:26,516
I will…

911
01:01:26,599 --> 01:01:28,267
drop out.

